## 9.2 Post-Hoc Power Analysis

A key question is whether SUGAR-MGH had adequate statistical power to
detect the SLC2A2 effect at genome-wide significance. If the study was
underpowered, the non-replication is uninformative; if well-powered, it
is evidence against a universal effect.

```{r power-analysis}
# Power calculation: ability of SUGAR-MGH to detect MetGen-sized effect
# Under H1: Z ~ N(beta / SE, 1)

beta_to_detect <- study_metgen$Beta       # 0.17 (MetGen effect)
se_sugar       <- sugar_slc2a2$SE         # 0.0481 (SUGAR-MGH precision)
ncp            <- beta_to_detect / se_sugar  # non-centrality parameter

# Power at three thresholds
thresholds <- c("Genome-wide (5e-8)" = 5e-8,
                "Relaxed (5e-7)"     = 5e-7,
                "Nominal (0.05)"     = 0.05)

power_results <- data.frame(
  Threshold = names(thresholds),
  Alpha     = thresholds,
  z_crit    = qnorm(1 - thresholds / 2),
  Power     = sapply(thresholds, function(alpha) {
    z <- qnorm(1 - alpha / 2)
    pnorm(z - ncp, lower.tail = FALSE) + pnorm(-z - ncp)
  }),
  row.names = NULL
)
power_results$Power_pct <- sprintf("%.1f%%", power_results$Power * 100)
power_results$Alpha <- sprintf("%.0e", power_results$Alpha)
kable(power_results[, c("Threshold", "Alpha", "Power_pct")],
      col.names = c("Threshold", "Alpha Level", "Power"),
      caption = "Statistical power of SUGAR-MGH to detect the MetGen effect size (Beta = 0.17)")

# Sample size needed for 80% power at genome-wide threshold
z_gw    <- qnorm(1 - 5e-8 / 2)      # = 5.4513
z_80    <- qnorm(0.80)               # = 0.8416
se_need <- beta_to_detect / (z_gw + z_80)
n_need  <- (se_sugar / se_need)^2 * 8269

cat(sprintf("Sample size required for 80%% power at 5e-8: N ~ %.0f\n", n_need))
cat(sprintf("SUGAR-MGH actual N: 8,269 (approximately %.1fx smaller than needed)\n", n_need / 8269))
```

